import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os
print(f'version cv2: {cv.__version__}')
image_path = 'src/Color.png'
image = cv.imread(image_path)
if image is None:
    print(f"   ! {image_path}")
else:
    N = image.shape[0]  
    M = image.shape[1]  
    C = image.shape[2]  
    print(f"  (N x M): {N} x {M} ")
    print(f" : {C}")
    file_size_bytes = os.path.getsize(image_path)
    file_size_kb = file_size_bytes / 1024    
    print(f"' '  : {file_size_bytes}  ({file_size_kb:.2f} )")
    image_rgb = cv.cvtColor(image, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    plt.imshow(image_rgb)
    plt.title(f"RGB-: {N}x{M}, {file_size_kb:.1f} KB")
    plt.show()

import cv2 as cv
import os
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

image_path = 'src/Color.png' 
image_bgr = cv.imread(image_path)
image_gray = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

if image_bgr is None:
    print(f":     {image_path}")
else:
    # 3 (RGB)
    print(f" 3 (RGB)")    
    height_rgb, width_rgb, channels_rgb = image_bgr.shape
    file_size_rgb = os.path.getsize(image_path)    
    print(f" (NxM):      {height_rgb} x {width_rgb}")
    print(f" : {channels_rgb}")
    print(f"'  :    {file_size_rgb} ")

    # 4 ()
    print(f" 4 ()")
    gray_path = 'src/Color_gray.png'
    cv.imwrite(gray_path, image_gray)    
    height_gray, width_gray = image_gray.shape
    file_size_gray = os.path.getsize(gray_path)    
    print(f" (NxM):      {height_gray} x {width_gray}")
    print(f" : 1")
    print(f"'  :    {file_size_gray} ")
    #
    print(f"")    
    print(f"  :RGB: {height_rgb}x{width_rgb} | Gray: {height_gray}x{width_gray}")
    print(f":    .")
    print(f"'  :RGB: {file_size_rgb} | Gray: {file_size_gray} ")
    ratio = file_size_rgb / file_size_gray
    print(f":  RGB  {ratio:.1f}  . ,  RGB  3    ,    1 .")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(image_bgr, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(f'RGB (3 )\n{file_size_rgb} ')
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(image_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f' (1 )\n{file_size_gray} ')    
    plt.show()

import cv2 as cv
import os
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import math

image_path = 'src/Color.png'   
n = 2                         
image_rgb = cv.imread(image_path)

if image_rgb is None:
    print(f"   ! {image_path}")
else:
    height_N, width_M, _ = image_rgb.shape
    file_size_original = os.path.getsize(image_path)

    print(f":")
    print(f" (N x M): {height_N} x {width_M}")
    print(f"' (): {file_size_original}  ({file_size_original/1024:.1f} KB)\n")

    new_width = math.floor(width_M / n)
    new_height = math.floor(height_N / n)
    new_dim = (new_width, new_height)
    image_resized = cv.resize(image_rgb, new_dim, interpolation=cv.INTER_AREA)
    
    print(f"   {n} .")
    print(f" :{new_height} x {new_width}\n")

    # 4.   
    resized_path = 'src/Color_resized.png'
    cv.imwrite(resized_path, image_resized, [cv.IMWRITE_PNG_COMPRESSION, 9])    
    file_size_resized = os.path.getsize(resized_path)
    print(f" :{resized_path}")
    print(f" ':{file_size_resized}  ({file_size_resized/1024:.1f} KB)\n")
    print(f"")
    if file_size_resized < file_size_original:
        diff = file_size_original - file_size_resized
        ratio = file_size_original / file_size_resized
        print(f", ' '   {diff}  ( {ratio:.1f} ).")
        print(":     4   n=2.")
        print("  =    ,    .")
    else:
        print(", ' '     .")

    # 6. 
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    
    # 
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(image_rgb, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(f'\n{height_N}x{width_M}')
    
    # 
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(image_resized, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(f' (1/{n})\n{new_height}x{new_width}')
    
    plt.show()

import cv2 as cv
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def resize_proportional(image, target_width):
    (h, w) = image.shape[:2]
    ratio = target_width / float(w)
    target_height = int(h * ratio)
    new_dimensions = (target_width, target_height)
    resized_img = cv.resize(image, new_dimensions, interpolation=cv.INTER_AREA)
    return resized_img

image_path = 'src/Color.png'
K = 100

image_bgr = cv.imread(image_path)

if image_bgr is None:
    print(f":     {image_path}")
else:
    image_resized_k = resize_proportional(image_bgr, K)
    
    print(f"  6")
    print(f" K: {K} ")
    print(f" (h x w): {image_bgr.shape[0]} x {image_bgr.shape[1]}")
    print(f" (h x w): {image_resized_k.shape[0]} x {image_resized_k.shape[1]}")
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(image_resized_k, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(f'  (Width={K}px)')
    plt.show()    
    cv.imwrite(f'src/Color_width.png', image_resized_k)
    print(f"   src/Color_width.png")

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

image_path = 'src/Zalik.png' 
image = cv.imread(image_path)

if image is None:
    print(f":    {image_path}")
else:
    rows, cols, ch = image.shape
    print(f" : {cols}x{rows}")

    print("  ")

    pts_input_affine = np.float32([
        [415, 340],
        [573, 342],
        [410, 540]
    ])

    pts_output_affine = np.float32([
         [150, 220],
        [450, 210],
        [140, 600]
    ])

    M_affine = cv.getAffineTransform(pts_input_affine, pts_output_affine)
    img_affine = cv.warpAffine(image, M_affine, (cols, rows))

    cv.imwrite('src/Zalik_affine.jpg', img_affine)

    print("  ")

    pts_input_persp = np.float32([
       [330, 210],   
        [520, 215],  
        [330, 460],   
        [520, 465]   
    ])

    width_new, height_new = 300, 400
    
    pts_output_persp = np.float32([
        [0, 0],
        [width_new, 0],
        [0, height_new],
        [width_new, height_new]
    ])

    M_persp = cv.getPerspectiveTransform(pts_input_persp, pts_output_persp)
    img_perspective = cv.warpPerspective(image, M_persp, (width_new, height_new))

    cv.imwrite('src/Zalik_perspective.jpg', img_perspective)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(image, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title("")
    plt.grid(True)
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img_affine, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title("")

    plt.subplot(1, 3, 3)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img_perspective, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title("")

    plt.show()
    print("    src/")
